One More Plot of Political Coup in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- The pro-U.S. conservative forces in south Korea are now framing a plot to postpone or scuttle the "National Assembly election" by cooking up a shocking incident targeted against the DPRK, according to a U.S. scenario.
 Commenting on this, Rodong Sinmun Tuesday brands this as another plot of political coup designed to preserve the pro-U.S. ultra-right conservative camp against the desire of the south Korean people for social progress and political reform and, on this basis, go back to the era of fascist dictatorship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The news analyst says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ultra-right conservative forces would stop at nothing however base to save themselves. Not without reason did a political party figure warn some time ago that the Grand National Party, going to excess, might declare refusal or boycott of the "election." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attention should be paid to the United States as regards the unpredictable unstable political situation in south Korea now. The U.S., the backstage wirepuller of the "impeachment against the president" and, at the same time, the mastermind of the plot to foil the "election," is resorting to vicious moves including the escalation of the military tension on the Korean peninsula to deliver the ultra-right conservative forces out of the tight corner by taking advantage of the current political confusion in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean people should see through the criminal scheme of the despicable traitors indulged in anti-reunification confrontation and corruption with the backing of the U.S., check and frustrate it at the right moment and sternly judge the traitorous group in the course of the forthcoming "election."

Founding Anniversary of Conservation Office of RMC Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- A meeting was held at the People's Palace of Culture on April 5 to commemorate the 50th anniversary of the Conservation Office of the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery.
 The cemetery located on Mt. Taesong in Pyongyang is a grand monument associated with the noble intentions and immortal leadership exploits of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il to perpetuate the memory of the anti-Japanese revolutionary forerunners and carry forward the revolutionary traditions of Juche generation after generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The office, founded on April 5, Juche 43 (1954), contributed to glorifying forever the great leadership exploits of the Party and the leader and the lofty revolutionary spirit of the anti-Japanese revolutionary forerunners through the conservation and management of the cemetery and education at it in the past 50 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meeting a congratulatory message of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea to officials and employees of the office was conveyed by Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the C.C. of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A report was made at the meeting and then followed speeches.

Functions Held Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- A meeting, round-table talks, seminar, lecture, photo exhibition and film show were held in Mongolia, Indonesia, Mexico, Ecuador, Peru and Uganda from March 17 until 29 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun and the 11th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK.
 The vice-chairman of the Mongolian-Korean Friendship Society in a speech at the meeting said that President Kim Il Sung was a great leader who set out on the road of revolution at his young age, defeated the Japanese and U.S. imperialisms and achieved the cause of founding the Party, the state and the army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted that the President founded the Juche idea and fully applied it to all sectors of the revolution and construction to build Korea into a powerful country, independent, self-supporting and self-reliant in national defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general secretary of the Communists Party of Mexico said at the round-table talks that the Songun policy of leader Kim Jong Il is drawing keen interest of the world political and social circles today because socialism in the DPRK is wining victory after victory despite the persistent anti-socialist moves of the U.S.-led imperialist allied forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the General Kim Jong Il Peruvian Amicable Institute said: it would have been unthinkable without Kim Jong Il, chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK, that socialism in the DPRK continues to advance dynamically thanks to the powerful military force. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting held in Mongolia.. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A book, photo and handicraft exhibition of the DPRK opened in Sonnechnogorsk City of Moscow Region on April 2. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed there were famous works of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and photos showing their immortal exploits, books and photos introducing the achievements made by the people and army of the DPRK in their efforts and handicrafts which bear witness to the resourcefulness and skills of Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Siham Ahmad Mugahed, chairman of the Egypt-Korea Friendship Association, issued a statement on March 28 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.

KCNA Assails U.S. "Defense Strategy" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- The Bush administration is persistently resorting to grave military adventure threatening humankind.
 The U.S. Defense Department worked out the "1-4-2-1 defense strategy", according to a recent issue of the Los Angeles Times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was revised and supplemented last year on the basis of the reexamination of the defense strategy dating back to the era of the Cold War and the period of the Clinton administration. Its keynote is to spark disputes in any place anytime and bring down the systems of the countries it aims to seize, according to its option. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This new defense strategy being the core of the U.S. strategy for world supremacy is arousing deep concern of the world public for its unprecedentedly adventurous and aggressive nature and aim and ways to carry it out as it is a strategy for preemptive nuclear attacks on different countries at the same time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The danger of this defense strategy lies in that it calls for conducting special and secret operations and using nukes as basic war methods according to the theory of preemptive strike and turning the U.S. military forces into active offensive forces, not reaction forces, as they have already been beefed up to the fullest extent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The strategy is aimed to expand the simultaneous operation capacity in the two regions during the Clinton administration to the one in the four regions. It calls for creating a smaller strike group equipped with powerful precision strike and latest information means, deploying it in an overseas base and organically combining the U.S. Central Intelligence Agency with irregular military forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As already known, the Afghan and Iraqi wars are no more than a prelude to realizing the U.S. military strategy for world supremacy after the demise of the Cold War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After occupying Afghanistan and Iraq through the brigandish wars of aggression, the U.S. is set to carry into practice its strategy for world supremacy by putting the Middle East and Northeast Asia under its full control and, furthermore, containing big powers around the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is by no means accidental that foreign media termed the new defense strategy a "very dangerous defense operation" as it involves preemptive strike, preemptive nuclear attack operation going beyond diplomacy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK and China are the major targets of the new defense strategy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the U.S. defense strategy the DPRK and China are made major targets of strategic operation and a plan has already been worked out to strike the DPRK and China with nuclear and conventional weapons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. revised the "Iraq + North Korea operation plan" it had already worked out as the "Iran + North Korea operation plan." It is escalating the nuclear confrontation with the DPRK behind the scene of dialogue. It is working with bloodshot eyes to put into practice the strategy for preemptive nuclear attack to stifle the DPRK by force of arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no doubt that the U.S. naval missile interceptor system to be deployed in the East Sea of Korea and other reckless military moves including joint military exercises under different codenames are quite contrary to its talk about the "negotiated settlement of the nuclear issue" and the U.S. design to stifle the DPRK remains unchanged. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality clearly shows what a reckless and dangerous phase the U.S. moves for a war of aggression against the DPRK have reached. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will take a decisive self-defensive countermeasure to avert a war and defend peace in the Korean peninsula and in the rest of Northeast Asia.

Open Letter to All People Released 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- The Emergency Measure Committee for the "General Election" of the Central Committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea on April 3 issued an "open letter to all the people" as regards the 17th "general election" to be held in south Korea.
 The "general election" will be held under the complicated situation caused in the wake of the passage of the "motion on impeachment against the president" unprecedented in the history of the constitution, the open letter said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The 17th "general election" means a turning point in history for our people as it will decide on whether or not they will put an end to the corrupt politics characterized by corruption and crimes and open a new chapter for politics of progress and reform and a scene of a decisive battle to foil the U.S. interference in the internal affairs of south Korea and build a democratic "national assembly" on their own efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the people should turn out as one in the struggle to check and frustrate the plot of the U.S. and the right-wing conservative forces to scuttle the "general election" and achieve a victory in the "general election". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Let's conclude the struggle against the impeachment with victory in 'general election'!" and "Let's build the national assembly without pro-U.S. conservative political parties!" This is the slogan to be put up in the "general election" and the aim to be attained by them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pro-U.S. conservative forces still remain the target of the people's campaign, the open letter said, calling upon all the people from all walks of life to totally bury the pro-U.S. conservative parties including the Grand National Party and the Democratic Party in the campaign for voting down their candidates and letting the pro-democracy and pro-reunification candidates win in the election. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the people should exert every effort to check the U.S. interference in the internal affairs of south Korea and its plot to scuttle the "general election", not to allow the U.S. to interfere in it even a bit but resolutely shatter the moves of the forces seeking the impeachment to postpone or torpedo it and conduct a dynamic nationwide struggle to hold it as scheduled. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It stressed the need for all the people to turn out as one to conclude the struggle against the "impeachment" with a victory in the "general election" and open a new horizon of independence, democracy and reunification.

Stronger Unity of Whole Nation Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- Papers here today dedicated articles to the 11th anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's work "The 10-Point Programme of the Great Unity of the Whole Nation for the Reunification of the Country."
 This work published on April 6, Juche 82 (1993) clarifies the idea that all those concerned about the destiny of the nation should unite as members of the nation transcending all their differences and work together to pave the way for national reunification. The work defines it as the general goal of the great unity of the whole nation to found a unified state, independent, peace-loving and neutral, and considers patriotism and the spirit of national independence as the ideological basis of unity. The work indicates specific ways for achieving the great unity of the nation such as the principle of attaining it by promoting co-existence, co-prosperity and common interests and subordinating everything to the cause of national reunification and issues of putting an end to all political disputes and building confidence and achieving unity between the north and the south, letting all Koreans join hands with each other for reunification irrespective of differing isms, developing contact, visits and dialogue, strengthening the solidarity among them and highly honoring those who have contributed to the cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 10-point programme serves as the most just programme of the great unity of the whole nation acceptable to everybody desirous of reunification for the patriotic will, the  idea of great unity and the fair and aboveboard nature and actual possibility reflected
in it, says Rodong Sinmun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All Koreans in the north and the south and overseas should wage a more vigorous struggle for the unity of the nation, peace of the country and national reunification under the banner of the Korean nation-first spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cooperation the Korean nation should realize is cooperation among Koreans against foreign forces as it is aimed at achieving harmony and unity among them to reject aggressive foreign forces and promote the cause of independent reunification in the basic spirit of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration. All Koreans should make redoubled efforts to put an end to the treacherous cooperation with the U.S. in south Korea and realize harmony and national cooperation for reunification under the banner of the Korean nation-first spirit in order to give spurs to the development of the national history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson calls on all Koreans to strengthen the national cooperation under the banner of the Korean nation-first spirit and thus build the structure of the Korean nation's confrontation with the U.S. through practical actions.

Japan's Moves to Repeat History of Aggression under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- The Japanese reactionaries stated with wild elation that "in case north Korea attacked Japan, it and the United States would join to annihilate the invading enemy in two weeks," declaring that recently staged  Japan-U.S. joint military exercise codenamed "Yamasakura-45" had ended in "an overall victory."
 A commentary of Rodong Sinmun today says that this hysterics well shows the reckless and grave nature of the Japanese reactionaries' moves to stage a comeback to Korea and their plan to realize it, in actuality, is entering into a practical stage, not remaining in operational concept or a preparatory stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The news analyst goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The braggadocio of the Japanese reactionaries that they would "annihilate" the Korean People's Army in two weeks is by no means confined to the latest joint war game. This opened to the public the aggressive plan against the DPRK jointly worked out and promoted by the U.S. and Japan and revealed the Japanese reactionaries' wild ambition to carry into practice their design to stage a comeback to Korea at any cost with the backing of the U.S. The ugly torrent of provocative words coming from Japan that "there is nothing wrong in launching a war against north Korea" and "Japan should make a preemptive attack on north Korea before it suffers damages" are not outcries of a few individual ultra-right reactionaries but representation of the Japanese reactionaries' consciousness of aggression against the DPRK pent up in the marrow of their bones and an open war agitation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan was and is a sworn enemy of the Korean people. The army and people of the DPRK will mete out a hundred-fold punishment to the Japanese reactionaries if they dare infringe upon its sovereignty even a little to give vent to the century-old wrath against Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Then the U.S would not be able to save Japan from the lot of destruction. The Japanese reactionaries had better ponder over the matter, mindful that their reinvasion of Korea would lead them to the second "Yasukuni Shrine."

U.S. Much Ado about "Threat from North Korea" Refuted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- Laporte, commander of the U.S. Armed Forces in South Korea, at a recent discussion on the defense budget of the Armed Services Committee of the U.S. House of Representatives asserted that the threat of missile attack from north Korea or its danger will remain even after the transfer of armed forces in south Korea to the areas south of the River Han as this threat is posed to the whole of the Korean peninsula. Minju Joson today says this in a signed commentary.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As far as the DPRK's missiles are concerned, they are not for threatening or attacking others but for protecting the national sovereignty and dignity from enemy invasion and serves as a deterrent force for frustrating the reckless moves of aggressors to provoke a war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has never posed any missile threat to anybody. It has never threatened the United States with missiles nor browbeaten south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The target of the DPRK's deterrence with missiles is only those foreign forces which infringe upon its national sovereignty and dignity. It is an inviolable legitimate right of a sovereign state to have missiles for national defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is not the DPRK but the United States that is creating a missile threat and increasing the danger of war on the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States should stop fooling the public at home and abroad with the fiction of "nuclear threat from north Korea" whose hypocritical and deceptive nature has already brought to light but withdraw from south Korea with its armed forces, the main source of aggression and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The People's Army and people of the DPRK will further increase the defence capability for self-defence in view of all sorts of reckless moves of the U.S. to start a new war in Korea. Should the aggressors ignite a war, they will react to it with a decisive counter-attack.

Japan's "Diplomatic Blue Paper" Slammed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- Japan in the "Diplomatic Blue Paper" for 2004 released recently again pulled up the DPRK, pretending to be interested in world peace and stability.
 Minju Joson today in a signed commentary says in this regard: This is, in essence, another political plot to brand the DPRK as the principal disturber of peace and stability in Northeast Asia and the rest of the world, justify its hostile policy towards the DPRK aimed to stifle it under that pretext and, furthermore, realize its wild ambition for militaristic overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK was compelled to take a legitimate self-defensive measure to defend the sovereignty of the country and the security of the state. Japan, however, is escalating its hostile policy towards it, faulting even this. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is clearly proved by the fact that Japan is set to pass the "bill on banning the portcall of specified ships" through the Diet in the wake of its passage of the "amendment to the law on foreign exchange," a bill on economic sanctions against the DPRK, in a bid to isolate and suffocate the DPRK economically. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Through this, Japan seeks to completely blockade the DPRK, form an international siege to it and realize military cooperation with the U.S. aimed at stifling the DPRK in a bid to settle the issue of the bilateral relations by force of arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
��Yet, Japan is pulling up the DPRK, paying lip-service to world peace and stability. This reminds one of a thief shouting "Stop the thief!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Japan is chiefly to blame for having rendered the situation in and around the Korean peninsula unstable.  All sorts of anti-DPRK hostile acts perpetrated by Japan along with its smear campaign against it only disclose its stance and true colours as a harasser of peace before the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  If Japan is truly interested in peace and stability in the region it should not drive the situation to a crisis but liquidate its crime-woven past in the basic spirit of the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration, abandon its ambition to emerge a military power and realize overseas expansion and stop blindly toeing the U.S. hostile policy towards the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Japan is well advised to think twice about what it should do before pulling up the DPRK.

Friendly Meeting with Staff Members of Cuban Embassy
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- A friendly meeting with staff members of the Cuban embassy here was held at the Pyongyang Koryo Hotel today by the International Department of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea on the occasion of the 11th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK.
 Invited to the meeting were Esteban Lobaina Romero, Cuban ambassador e.p. to the DPRK, and staff members of the Cuban embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present were Pak Kyong Son, vice department director of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Before the meeting, the participants saw a Korean documentary film "Great Change under the Songun Revolutionary Leadership".

Famous Porcelain Centre
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- The Porcelain Production of the Mansudae Art Studio is well known in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 It was organized in April Juche 63 (1974) to inherit the traditional techniques of famous Korean ceramics and to further develop them to suit the modern aesthetics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under deep care of leader Kim Jong Il, who values the national traditions, it was made up of 10-odd porcelain technicians including U Chi Son who were picked from different factories in the country. Over the last three decades, it has steadily been reinforced with more technicians and made ceramics famous in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the production includes Im Sa Jun who is well known at home and abroad and scores of competent ceramists and skilful craftsmen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Producing many ceramics strong in national tincture and unique in style and content, they have paved a new phase of modern ceramic workmanship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, Koryo celadon earned its fame in the modern Koryo celadon show of two ceramists, the modern Koryo celadon and famous paintings exhibition for 89 and the modern Korean art exhibition held in Japan in the 1980s. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Gourd-shaped kettle" and "vase decorated with earrings" were highly appreciated in the international exhibition of inventions held in Moscow in 1987 and in a world contest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The production makes not only Koryo celadon but also traditional ceramics such as those of the Ri dynasty, Hoeryong earthenware used by the Korean people from olden times, vases of different shapes and ceramic sculpture, and other ceramics for decoration and daily use. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has also made such extra-large ceramics as celadon vase inlaid with a pine tree and crane". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its products are very popular in foreign markets.

Ceremony of Starting Restoration of Singye Temple Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- A ceremony of starting the restoration of Singye Temple to its former glory was held in Mt. Kumgang resort Tuesday.
 It began with a Buddhist ritual. Then its attendants heard a report on the restoration of the temple, an introduction of its outline, a congratulatory speech and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Buddhists from the north and the south of Korea, officials in the field of the preservation of historical and cultural relics and those concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that Buddhists and officials of the institutions concerned in the north and the south have met in the same place to hold the ceremony, speakers added that this provided an occasion of demonstrating at home and abroad the fact that if Koreans pool their will and wisdom as a homogeneous nation which has created one and the same culture from olden times, they can not only restore the ancient cultural heritages of the nation to their original state, preserve and further develop them but bring earlier the day of national reunification through national cooperation.

Memorial Service Held for Revolutionary Fighter O Paek Ryong
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- A national memorial service was held at the People's Palace of Culture today to commemorate the 20th death anniversary of revolutionary fighter O Paek Ryong.
 O was a man who single-heartedly remained loyal to President Kim Il Sung with true unblemished conscience and sense of obligation free from any affectation and changing attitude during the two hard-fought revolutionary wars and in the days of arduous revolution and construction at various stages and a genuine revolutionary who dedicated himself to implementing to the letter the Juche-oriented revolutionary line of the Workers' Party of Korea in the army building, national defence build-up, power construction and economic construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Born to a poor peasant family in Hoeryong County, North Hamgyong Province (at that time) on October 24, 1914, he joined the Korean People's Revolutionary Army at the beginning of the anti-Japanese armed struggle. He grew up to be a platoon, company and regiment commander from an ordinary soldier, displaying matchless heroism and self-sacrificing spirit in the anti-Japanese war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the country's liberation he devotedly worked to build the regular armed forces and defend the gains of the revolution, true to the line of building the army set forth by President Kim Il Sung. Assuming the heavy responsibility as divisional commander of the Korean People's Army during the rigorous Fatherland Liberation War, he contributed to repelling the U.S. imperialists' armed invasion and winning a victory in the war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He performed great feats in safeguarding the headquarters of the revolution and increasing the military power of the country, holding important posts at the Ministry of Home Affairs, the Ministry of National Defence, the Central Committee of the WPK, the National Defence Commission of the Central People's Committee, and other Party, state and military institutions in the post war period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, in his memorial address said that the revolutionary life of O Paek Ryong was a life of a genuine revolutionary who dedicated his all to the Party, the leader, the country and the people and to the victory of the cause of socialism and a worthwhile life which showed in practice how revolutionaries should uphold the leader and protect him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underscored the need to carry forward the transparent outlook on the leader and the indomitable revolutionary spirit displayed by O Paek Ryong and other anti-Japanese revolutionary forerunners and push ahead with the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche under the uplifted banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The memorial service was attended by senior officials of the Party, the state and the army and anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A wreath was place before his bust in the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong on the same day.
